race.comment: WRENLEE (5) resumes for his second campaign. The debut run over 1000m at Cranbourne was very good when just missing before perhaps finding 1200m in town a bridge too far last time. He should be an improver this time around in a winnable race. KADESH (11) is a filly by Toronado on debut for the Hayes yard. She's won a Pakenham jumpout leading in and has to be respected for the top yard. NEVILLE BARTOS (4) is a King's Legacy gelding on debut for the Hayes yard. He was given a solid hitout and won a Seymour jump out a few weeks ago in preparation for this. Drawn well and can figure. TENNESSEE SONG (13) is a filly by American Pharoah on debut for the Dabernig yard. She's jumped out well and Meech is booked from the inside gate which is noteworthy. BRINSON (9) is a filly by I Am Immortal on debut for the Kennewell yard who looked good winning a recent trial at Caulfield Heath. Tricky draw but looks sharp and can win.
